SCHC Annual Fair on the Square
October 18, 2015 at 8:55 PM ·

We would be nothing without our vendors. We appreciate each and every one of you. For that reason, Laura does her best to fix any problems so that our vendors are happy. She works hard to ensure they are taken care of and can only fix what is brought to her attention. Please feel free to let us know if there is a way to make our vendors even more happy. She is always open to New ideas. We do apologize for the low traffic this year. it seems to have been a trend everywhere this year. We hope everyone made some money and left happy.

post_text: We would like to thank everyone who came out for the Marking of the Inn by the DAC. A special Thank you to Commissioner Jo Lee Williams, Elaine Gillespie, and The Philadelphia Baptist Church Choir. Thank you to the local City Council Members (Barbara Cullifer, Flossy Brown, and Debbie Stone) for your support, as well as Jimmy Lee from the County Commissioner's. It is always heartwarming to know we have the support from City and County representatives as well as the citizens of the city and county who came out. Thank you to our members who came and celebrated and helped make things run so smoothly.
text: We would like to thank everyone who came out for the Marking of the Inn by the DAC. A special Thank you to Commissioner Jo Lee Williams, Elaine Gillespie, and The Philadelphia Baptist Church Choir. Thank you to the local City Council Members (Barbara Cullifer, Flossy Brown, and Debbie Stone) for your support, as well as Jimmy Lee from the County Commissioner's. It is always heartwarming to know we have the support from City and County representatives as well as the citizens of the city and county who came out. Thank you to our members who came and celebrated and helped make things run so smoothly.

Santa Claus is coming to town December 21st. There will be some vendors to do your last minute shopping with.... Inn admission is $5 for the general public and Free to Members and Vendors.

post_text: The leader of the ghost hunting group Southern Crescent Paranormal has sent us some pictures taken with her camera. they will be posted later today with her comments on them. Unfortunately she did not submit a formal report. Other members that are no longer with the group will be submitting a report of their findings though. Two of our members joined this couple at different times, and both had personal experiences. Even though the leader of this group was a disappointment, there were some good investigators who did a professional job as part of her team. Findings submitted will follow today.

post_text: We would like to thank the Southern Crescent Paranormal group for the exciting ghost last night/this morning. It was a learning experience for those allowed to attend. It seems that the most activity is in the Jail and in the Inn. As soon as all the evidence is examined, it will be submitted to us to share with you. The group had asked to return in cooler weather because of all of the activity. We hope to start Ghost tours to the public this Halloween for a small fee.

Providence Canyon Geology Day
June 29, 2013
Providence Canyon is one of the great geographic wonders of the eastern United States. Join Professor Rich McWilliams of Thomas University in Thomasville, GA for a close-up view of this most unusual park. Pre-registration is required. $5 plus $5 parking. Call 229-838-4706 for more information.
